{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/why-context-matters/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Ordina Bold Tech & Design Blog","configs":{"countOfInitialPost":10}}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"7f177352-0cb7-5aa5-b6fd-cfd77443938a","excerpt":"Introduction Imagine visiting a museum and the floor plan gives no indication of the floors in the building, which collections are located where, or what the different routes are through the museum. Or smartphones that get so big you can’t operate them with one hand? Then think…","html":"<h2 id=\"introduction\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#introduction\" aria-label=\"introduction permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Introduction</h2>\n<p>Imagine visiting a museum and the floor plan gives no indication of the floors in the building, which collections are located where, or what the different routes are through the museum. Or smartphones that get so big you can’t operate them with one hand? Then think about all the situations where you use your smartphone with only one hand.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 780px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.41025641025641%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Contex blog 1\"\n        title=\"Contex blog 1\"\n        src=\"/static/fb0638fb4a7999283eba2506a658c599/be796/Contex_blog_1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/fb0638fb4a7999283eba2506a658c599/4146e/Contex_blog_1.jpg 195w,\n/static/fb0638fb4a7999283eba2506a658c599/e52b6/Contex_blog_1.jpg 390w,\n/static/fb0638fb4a7999283eba2506a658c599/be796/Contex_blog_1.jpg 780w,\n/static/fb0638fb4a7999283eba2506a658c599/ad68d/Contex_blog_1.jpg 1170w,\n/static/fb0638fb4a7999283eba2506a658c599/62522/Contex_blog_1.jpg 1560w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"context-is-what-gives-meaning-to-design\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#context-is-what-gives-meaning-to-design\" aria-label=\"context is what gives meaning to design permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Context is what gives meaning to design</h2>\n<p>A product or a service that does not consider the context in which it will be used is often not clear, less user-friendly, or even completely redundant. And conversely, when the design of a product or service fails to provide context on how it should be used, it also fails in its purpose. <strong>Even though design and context are inextricably linked, we still too often encounter situations in which design and context are not related</strong>.</p>\n<p>To start, let’s look at the general definition of context. Citing Wikipedia: Context is the larger, meaning-giving framework within which something takes place”</p>\n<p>But what does this mean for design and more specifically user centered design? There are two ways we can approach context in design:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>“A product or service that does not consider the context in which it will be used is often not clear, les user-friendly, or even completely redundant.”</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"1-know-the-context-you-are-designing-for\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#1-know-the-context-you-are-designing-for\" aria-label=\"1 know the context you are designing for permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1. Know the context you are designing for</h2>\n<p>This is about how the design of a product or service <strong>fits within a larger set of situations and circumstances that affect its use</strong>. These external drivers make up the specifications for the design together with, among other things, the technical &#x26; business requirements.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What does the user think, feel, hope for at the time of interaction?</li>\n<li>In what situations is it used? Relax at home, on the go, during a workout or in stressful situations?</li>\n<li>Does the interaction require a high or a low level of cognitive effort?</li>\n<li>What type of device is being used?</li>\n<li>What is the frequency of use?</li>\n<li>Do we need to take into account certain limitations of the users and so on.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If we look at the context in which our museum floorplan is used, we can say that most visitors visit the museum only once. In addition, a museum can be a busy environment with many auditory and visual stimuli. Also, it is not always easy to follow the predetermined route through the museum. Or you just want to find the nearest toilet because one of your kids suddenly must go urgently. Contradictory as it may sound, visiting a museum can be an intense experience. In all these cases, a well-designed floor plan can offer visitors a place of rest and a foothold during their visit.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 780px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.41025641025641%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"A museum can be a busy environment with lots of stimuli. Photo credit: Natural history museum\"\n        title=\"A museum can be a busy environment with lots of stimuli. Photo credit: Natural history museum\"\n        src=\"/static/49ea753ba83796659210467048bd429a/be796/22588385802_a2b9a4d0ec_b.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/49ea753ba83796659210467048bd429a/4146e/22588385802_a2b9a4d0ec_b.jpg 195w,\n/static/49ea753ba83796659210467048bd429a/e52b6/22588385802_a2b9a4d0ec_b.jpg 390w,\n/static/49ea753ba83796659210467048bd429a/be796/22588385802_a2b9a4d0ec_b.jpg 780w,\n/static/49ea753ba83796659210467048bd429a/ad68d/22588385802_a2b9a4d0ec_b.jpg 1170w,\n/static/49ea753ba83796659210467048bd429a/62522/22588385802_a2b9a4d0ec_b.jpg 1560w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>A museum can be a busy environment with lots of stimuli. Photo credit: Natural history museum</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h2 id=\"2-provide-a-clear-context-within-your-design\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#2-provide-a-clear-context-within-your-design\" aria-label=\"2 provide a clear context within your design permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. Provide a clear context within your design</h2>\n<p>Just like you need to know the context you are designing for, it is important that the way the product or service is designed in turn also provides the right context. So that the way it is to be <strong>used and interpreted is clear</strong>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What is the product intended to do?</li>\n<li>What is expected of the user? What should he do?</li>\n<li>What actions does he have to complete?</li>\n<li>How does he have to interpret and operate it and so on</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Again, our floor plan provides a good casus. The usefulness of a floor plan is to give visitors a means of orientation, preferably with as little effort as possible to interpret it. Just working with numbers without anything of further description is not enough in this case. What can help is to name the floors, clearly indicate where to find the different collections and what the recommended routes are for visiting the museum. This gives enough information both for people who want to follow their route deliberately and for visitors who want to wander freely but still benefit from a general overview of the museum.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 780px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 68.20512820512819%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"A well designed floorplan provides sufficient context so it can easily be interpreted and helps form a mental model of the museum. Photo credit: gundiscover.com\"\n        title=\"A well designed floorplan provides sufficient context so it can easily be interpreted and helps form a mental model of the museum. Photo credit: gundiscover.com\"\n        src=\"/static/08146cf72e835777000d02ed0d5129ce/be796/Plattegrond-Natuur-historisch-museum-Londen.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/08146cf72e835777000d02ed0d5129ce/4146e/Plattegrond-Natuur-historisch-museum-Londen.jpg 195w,\n/static/08146cf72e835777000d02ed0d5129ce/e52b6/Plattegrond-Natuur-historisch-museum-Londen.jpg 390w,\n/static/08146cf72e835777000d02ed0d5129ce/be796/Plattegrond-Natuur-historisch-museum-Londen.jpg 780w,\n/static/08146cf72e835777000d02ed0d5129ce/ad68d/Plattegrond-Natuur-historisch-museum-Londen.jpg 1170w,\n/static/08146cf72e835777000d02ed0d5129ce/62522/Plattegrond-Natuur-historisch-museum-Londen.jpg 1560w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>A well designed floorplan provides sufficient context so it can easily be interpreted and helps form a mental model of the museum. Photo credit: gundiscover.com</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h2 id=\"how-can-you-build-this-in-your-workflow\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#how-can-you-build-this-in-your-workflow\" aria-label=\"how can you build this in your workflow permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How can you build this in your workflow?</h2>\n<p>In order to properly frame the context you are designing for, it is important for a design exercise to start from research and analysis. <strong>Customer journey mapping, service safaris, contextual interviews, observations</strong> are all techniques that can be used to map the external context and build a good situational sketch on how a product or service will be used.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 780px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 64.61538461538461%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"A customer journey is a great tool to map the end-to-end journey of customers and understand the external context. Photo credit: aaslh.org\"\n        title=\"A customer journey is a great tool to map the end-to-end journey of customers and understand the external context. Photo credit: aaslh.org\"\n        src=\"/static/bf50eeffbf81dc8d04cd4b409236d505/be796/customer-journey-map-exploratorium.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bf50eeffbf81dc8d04cd4b409236d505/4146e/customer-journey-map-exploratorium.jpg 195w,\n/static/bf50eeffbf81dc8d04cd4b409236d505/e52b6/customer-journey-map-exploratorium.jpg 390w,\n/static/bf50eeffbf81dc8d04cd4b409236d505/be796/customer-journey-map-exploratorium.jpg 780w,\n/static/bf50eeffbf81dc8d04cd4b409236d505/ad68d/customer-journey-map-exploratorium.jpg 1170w,\n/static/bf50eeffbf81dc8d04cd4b409236d505/bc229/customer-journey-map-exploratorium.jpg 1554w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>A customer journey is a great tool to map the end-to-end journey of customers and understand the external context. Photo credit: aaslh.org</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>A well-designed product or service, that in turn provides clear, contextual information <strong>makes its purpose clear to the user, provides an intuitive and accessible user experience and offers sufficient support during use</strong>. This can be done by adjusting the display of information and features according to the device or the situation in which it is used, by applying accessibility best practices, by using labels and error messages consistently, by ensuring that the user does not get stuck thanks to a clear navigation and information architecture and so on.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 780px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 29.230769230769234%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Progress trackers provide context for users and help them understand the different steps in the process. Photo credit: medium.muz.li\"\n        title=\"Progress trackers provide context for users and help them understand the different steps in the process. Photo credit: medium.muz.li\"\n        src=\"/static/859f2ffa2bf905785a6769f27881ebe3/be796/1_QEitftIsAEaU57ShSwU4vg.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/859f2ffa2bf905785a6769f27881ebe3/4146e/1_QEitftIsAEaU57ShSwU4vg.jpg 195w,\n/static/859f2ffa2bf905785a6769f27881ebe3/e52b6/1_QEitftIsAEaU57ShSwU4vg.jpg 390w,\n/static/859f2ffa2bf905785a6769f27881ebe3/be796/1_QEitftIsAEaU57ShSwU4vg.jpg 780w,\n/static/859f2ffa2bf905785a6769f27881ebe3/ad68d/1_QEitftIsAEaU57ShSwU4vg.jpg 1170w,\n/static/859f2ffa2bf905785a6769f27881ebe3/62522/1_QEitftIsAEaU57ShSwU4vg.jpg 1560w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Progress trackers provide context for users and help them understand the different steps in the process. Photo credit: medium.muz.li</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h2 id=\"why-context-matters\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#why-context-matters\" aria-label=\"why context matters permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Why context matters</h2>\n<p>No matter how simple or complex a product or service is, from a map that helps you find your way in a museum to a smartphone that you use in so many different situations, <strong>when context and design are not linked, it will miss its purpose and then it will fail to meet the needs of the user</strong>.</p>\n<p>By considering the context in which it will be used, we create products and services that are directly <strong>rooted in the living environment</strong> of our users. It helps designers to clarify the problem as well as the scope and to create products that solve actual user needs.</p>\n<p><strong>I’m curious to know how context plays a role in your everyday design practice?</strong></p>","headings":[{"depth":2,"value":"Introduction","id":"introduction"},{"depth":2,"value":"Context is what gives meaning to design","id":"context-is-what-gives-meaning-to-design"},{"depth":2,"value":"1. Know the context you are designing for","id":"1-know-the-context-you-are-designing-for"},{"depth":2,"value":"2. Provide a clear context within your design","id":"2-provide-a-clear-context-within-your-design"},{"depth":2,"value":"How can you build this in your workflow?","id":"how-can-you-build-this-in-your-workflow"},{"depth":2,"value":"Why context matters","id":"why-context-matters"}],"frontmatter":{"title":"Why context matters","category":"User Experience (UX)","tags":["UX"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fullWidth","backgroundColor":"#d8d8d8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/4764192a9a1534da746814ed3754268f/